cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques for temporal information extraction in clinical notes. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also discusses the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and structured prediction, which are common techniques in machine learning and deep learning. This suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the use of distant supervision rules for predicting relations, which is a common technique in information retrieval (IR). Therefore, the paper could also be classified under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
